"""
Pure Python .std reader.

The reader is intentionally data-oriented: it parses the common input
sections into dictionaries and lists, while retaining source line numbers and
raw records so the same model can later be used as the basis for a writer.

Current coverage includes:
    - job information and units
    - joint coordinates
    - member incidences
    - element/plate incidences
    - group definitions
    - materials
    - member property/profile assignments
    - constants/material assignments
    - supports
    - member releases, offsets, fireproofing and truss/tension/compression lists
    - plane-stress element lists and inactive member commands
    - wind definition blocks (raw records retained)
    - load cases (incl. floor/oneway/reference load items), reference loads,
      load combinations and combination entries
    - steel/concrete design parameter blocks

Example:
    python code-miscellaneous/InteroperabilityWithSTDFile.py --file build/model.std
"""

